latestPosts.caption:
“Stand Up Mr. Khurana” has truly been the highlight of my year.

For someone who feared speaking on stage all her life, performing a two-hour play feels like a dream come true. I am beyond grateful to @sachinparikhofficial ji and @bhaktirathod_official for trusting me with Kanak. Even more so to my director, @swapnilbaraskar.26 Sir, who refined me as an actor and helped me tackle comedy, something I always found the toughest part of acting.

I never imagined this journey for myself, but it has made me believe that sometimes the best things just find their way to you. I’ve lived and loved every moment of this process.

After 15 years in the field, I feel so proud to call myself an artist. Ab bhi bohot kuch leke jaana baki hai, and I can’t wait to take it all on 💫🪬

latestPosts.caption:
It’s been over a year of living alone… some days I was just surviving, some days I was truly living but ever since she came, I’ve mostly just been loving.

People who know me, know what I went through with my last pet. It broke me in ways I couldn’t even explain. It took me years to heal, to gather the courage to open my heart again. I promised myself and I promised God, that next time I would be ready , ready to love better, to show up better.

And then she arrived. Out of nowhere. Like a blessing I didn’t even know I was ready for. Truly God sent, through this farishta @vaibhav3112 , who just called me one fine day and within an hour, she was home. And stayed. Forever.

I’ve changed in so many ways and I’m so grateful that I got this chance again.

My Shona , you’ve made this life alive and so much more beautiful.

Happy 6 to us ♾️🐾
